09/01/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Spain, Portugal and Greece have decided to completely open their labour markets to citizens of Bulgaria and Romania as of last week, according to an announcement from the European Commission press centre Thursday (January 8th). All three countries have a considerable number of workers from Bulgaria and Romania, most of them working illegally. The measure is mostly aimed at preventing harsh working conditions for them, according to the statement. (Netinfo, Darik - 08/01/09)
